,Recommended,262900,12091519,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,crorsina,"Good value.  Not exactly challenging, but there's enough to it to keep it engaging.  Both tracks of the soundtrack aren't obnoxious either, even after 40 hours.There is enough room for improvement left in this game that I would consider getting a sequel or expansion if one were released.  It'd be nice to have some metrics screens to help identify poorly performing employees, to be able to adjust schedules of several employees at once, to be able to see the previous day's performance again after you've closed the screen that comes up at midnight, and some way to more easily tell what hours you are over/under-staffed (especially with L2s!).There seem to be odd algorithm issues that could be improved, such as when you have multiple flowtubes and employees sometimes take unnecessarily long routes or when your elevators are upgraded and people get stuck on them quite awhile because of how the floor stops get queued.  Still, if you're a fan of casual tycoon/sim games, none of these are serious enough to ruin the game.The biggest obstacle I ran into was IT staff quitting frequently because of the poor performance of the elevators (I finally caved and built them their own elevator at the end of the IT wing of the building)."
