76561198304676872,Recommended,262900,34439393,Posted: 23 August,all,ridane2013,"I personally have worked in call center for 7 years. I was the guy who probly called you about Directv, Bank of America, or even sprint. Actually you called me because I was inbound not outbound. So what is actually cool about this game is you can name your Call Center whatever you want design it how you like and ultimatly run a call center. You will start by naming the call center setting up your 1st 3 rooms being inbound outbound and back office. In the call center world this doesnt always happen at the same site. It is ultimatly based on your contract. I have only ever had to do Inbound in most of why I did unless it was to call someone back. Now something that you will notice that is very real is that you will have a high turnover in this game, Why you may ask? Thats the Nature of the Beast in a call center either your worked to hard or not enough and youll defently experince this. Now as far as Gameplay is concerned it can be a bit slow at times and stacked against you do to the point you cant hire who you want when you want. you have to work to unlock all of this. In the call center world you would work from the ground up with HR Supervisors Opperations managers trainers QA teams and Tech. This is where the game loses it for me when you start out you have the option for IB OB and BO and thats it no HR no Supervisors to push no Opps managers no Trainers and for some reason this game doesnt have Quailty associates which is the key to a call center without Quality control that guy that is speaking with you on the phone could call you a dumb ignorant stupid head and there is nothing you could do about it except leave the company if that is your choice. So in Closing the game is good its not excellent or great it is good it delivers on some funny bits but it falls short on authenticty when it comes to the point of where you have to unlock everything. the game should be like here is your money build and thats it. so 3 stars out of 5 because it is fun youll have a good time playing it and there is a challenge the its not 5 stars because again lack of authenticty and the fact they make you unlock stuff that you need early on in the game. Do I recommend this game ? Yes especially if you work , have ever worked or are planning on working in a call center it will give you a bit of a taste or give you a parody of what it is like. Enjoy!"
