,Recommended,262900,35506087,Posted: 5 October,all,{BuFFerOverflow},"The game is fun for the micromanager. The kind of game you play casually a dozen hours then take a moment, sit back, and say ""behold! Look at what I have created!"" While it is a fun game and has given me many hours of fun, casual builder/management fun it becomes a little troublesome to manage when things get complex and large. To be specific it's hard to get a good idea of who's doing what and who's assigned to what.  Would be perfect for me if they had a little more options, as in graphs and data to manage things when the tower and employees get large.No game is perfect and the fact that I even wrote a review at all shows that it will be enjoyable if you're into casual simulator/micro-management builder games, just probably not a game you'll likely sink hundreds of hours into."
